It seems like you're asking about the traditional Fijian method of brewing kava, specifically during the time of peace negotiations. In Fijian culture, kava, also known as "yaqona," plays a significant role in ceremonies and social gatherings. During peace negotiations, the sharing of kava was a symbolic act representing unity and respect.

The process of preparing kava involves grinding the dried kava root into a fine powder, then mixing it with water in a large communal bowl, known as a "tanoa." The mixture is then strained through a cloth to remove any solid particles. The resulting liquid is a mildly sedative and euphoric beverage that is shared among the participants of the ceremony.

The act of sharing kava during peace negotiations was a way to show goodwill and a commitment to resolving conflicts peacefully. It was also a way to create a sense of community and shared purpose among the participants.

Na ivakarau ni Fakawela ena gauna ni tawase ni yabaki e dua na ivakarau vakavanua ka dau vakayacori ena veitikotiko vaka-Viti, se na iTaukei, me vakaraitaka na vakavinavinaka ki na Kalou kei na nodra qaravi na kalou ni nodra vanua ena vuku ni veika vinaka era sotava ena yabaki sa oti, ka kerea talega na veivakalougatataki ena yabaki vou sa tu mai.

Era daucakava na iTaukei na ivakarau ni Fakawela ena gauna ni tawase ni yabaki me baleta e vica na vuna bibi:

1. **Vakavinavinaka:** Me vakavinavinaka ki na Kalou kei na yalo ni nodra qase ena nodra vakarautaka na kakana, bula, kei na veika vinaka era sotava ena yabaki sa oti. Na Fakawela e dua na gauna ni vakavinavinaka ka vakarokoroko.

2. **Kerea na Veivakalougatataki:** Me kerea na veivakalougatataki, bula vinaka, kei na bula tawamudu mai na Kalou kei na yalo ni nodra qase ena yabaki vou. Era vakabauta ni na vukei ira na nodra masu kei na nodra cakacaka vakalotu me ra sotava na veika vinaka ena yabaki vou.

3. **Veivakasoqoni kei na Veivakaukauwataki ni Veitikotiko:** Na Fakawela e gauna talega ni veivakasoqoni ni vanua, veiwekani, kei na veikoro me ra vakayacora vata na soqo, kana, gunu, kei na meke. E vakaukauwataki kina na veiwekani kei na bula vakavanua ena nodra sota vata na lewenivanua.

4. **Veivakasavasavataki kei na Vakavoui:** E dau vakayacori talega na veivakasavasavataki ena gauna ni Fakawela, me vakatakilakilataka na tekivu vou. Oqo e rawa ni okati kina na veivakasavasavataki vakayalo, vakasama, kei na vakatubuqoroqoro, ka vakarautaka na vanua kei na lewenivanua me ra curuma na yabaki vou ena savasava kei na vakavoui ni yalo.

prompting_state.prompt: Sa daucakacakataki vakacava na ivakacavacava vei ira na tamata cakacaka i Viti?

Fijian.text:
Na ivakacavacava vei ira na tamata cakacaka i Viti e vakarautaki ena vuku ni lawa ka vakatulewataki ena Employment Relations Promulgation (ERP) 2007. Eso na ivakacavacava bibi era rawata na tamata cakacaka e Viti e okati kina:

1. **Kena Sau**: Na kena ituvatuva na isau e dodonu me vaka na kena ituvatuva ena lawa ni cakacaka, ka vakatautauvatataki kei na kena ituvaki na cakacaka kei na veivakatovolei e gadrevi.

2. **Siga ni Vakacegu kei na Siga ni Maroroi**: Na tamata cakacaka e dodonu me ra vakacegu ena dua na siga ena dua na macawa, vakavuqa ena Siga Tabu. Eso talega na siga ni maroroi vakalawa me vaka na Kirisimasi, Niu Iyia, kei na so tale na siga ni maroroi e vakarautaka na matanitu.

3. **Siga ni Galala kei na Siga ni Vakacegu Vakalawa**: E tiko na dodonu ni tamata cakacaka me ra taura na siga ni galala ena vuku ni tauvimate se na vakayagataki ni gauna ni cakacaka me vaka na veivakasucumi.

4. **Sasaga ni Veivakalolomataki kei na Veivakaduiduitaki**: Na ERP e vakarautaka na ivakarau ni veitaqomaki vei ira na tamata cakacaka mai na veivakalolomataki kei na veivakaduiduitaki ena vanua ni cakacaka.

Makogai Island was selected as a leper colony due to its remote location, which made it easier to isolate patients and prevent the spread of the disease to the rest of the population.

The leper colony on Makogai Island was established in 1911, and it remained in operation until 1969, when the Fijian government decided to close the colony and integrate people with leprosy back into their communities. During its operation, the colony provided medical treatment and care to hundreds of people affected by leprosy.

Today, Makogai Island is no longer a leper colony, and it has been restored to its natural state. The island is now a popular tourist destination, known for its beautiful beaches, coral reefs, and historic significance.

prompting_state.prompt: Na cava sa daugadrevi mena tauyavutaki na bisinisi lalai i Viti?

Fijian.text:
Na tauyavutaki ni bisinisi lalai i Viti, se na vanua cava ga, e rawa ni vakarautaka na veika vinaka vakalevu, ia e daugadrevi talega me vakasamataki vakavinaka na veika e rawa ni yaco. Eso na veika bibi me daugadrevi ena tauyavutaki ni bisinisi lalai i Viti e okati kina:

1. **Vakarautaki ni iLavo:** Na kena vakarautaki na ilavo me baleta na vakatekivu kei na vakacurumi ni bisinisi e dua na ituvaki bibi. E rawa ni dredre na kena kunei na ilavo vakacakacaka se na veivuke ni lavo mai na baqe se vei ira na dau soli dinau, vakabibi kevaka e sega ni dua na itukutuku ni bisinisi se na ivakadinadina ni bula vinaka ni bisinisi.

2. **Vakadidike kei na Vakatorocaketaki ni Makete:** E bibi me kilai vinaka na makete, oka kina na kena kilai na kedra ivakarau ni bula na kasitama, na veisisivi, kei na veika e gadrevi ena makete. Na sega ni vakayacori ni vakadidike vakamaqosa e rawa ni vakavuna na leqa ena nodra vakatorocaketaki na ivoli se na veiqaravi e sega ni veiganiti kei na nodra gagadre na kasitama.

3. **Vakadonui kei na Lawa:** Na kena gadrevi me muria na bisinisi na lawa kei na ivakavuvuli ni vanua, oka kina na kena vakadonui na bisinisi, na laiseni, na vakacavacava, kei na ivakatakilakila ni veitaqomaki ni cakacaka. Na kena sega ni muria na lawa e rawa ni vakavuna na tarovi ni bisinisi se na totogitaki.

4. **Veisisivi:** Na veisisivi ena makete e rawa ni kaukaua, vakabibi mai vei ira na bisinisi lelevu era sa tu vakarau ena makete. Na kena vakatorocaketaki na ivoli se veiqaravi vou, se na kena vakavinakataki na veiqaravi sa tu, e rawa ni gadrevi me rawa ni veisisivi kina.

5. **Vakayagataki ni Tekinolaji:** Na kena vakayagataki vakavuku na tekinolaji e rawa ni vakalevutaka na noda rawa ni cakacaka kei na veiqaravi vei ira na kasitama. Na sega ni vakayagataki vinaka na tekinolaji e rawa ni vakavuna na bisinisi me bera na veisisivi.

6. **Vakatorocaketaki ni Nodra Vakavulici na Lewenivanua:** Na kena vakatorocaketaki na nodra vakavulici na lewenivanua e tiko ena bisinisi, me rawa ni ra vakayacora vinaka na nodra cakacaka ka ra vakarautaka na veiqaravi vinaka vei ira na kasitama.

7. **Veisau ni iYau ni Vanua kei na Vakacaca ni Draki:** Na bisinisi lalai e rawa ni vakaleqai vakalevu mai na veisau ni iYau ni vanua kei na vakacaca ni draki, vakabibi ena vanua e vakataki Viti e dau sotava na cava, waluvu, kei na veika tale eso ni draki katakata.

Na kena vakasamataki vinaka na veika oqo kei na kena vakayacori na vakarautaki vinaka e rawa ni vukea na bisinisi lalai me tubu ka bula vinaka ena makete e Viti.

Na cava sa daugadrevi mena tauyavutaki na bisinisi lalai i Viti? E vuqa na ka e rawa ni dau vakavuna me dredre na tauyavutaki ni bisinisi lalai e Viti. Eso na vuna bibi e okati kina:

1. **Lack of Access to Finance (Dravudravua ni iLavo ni Veivuke)**: E levu na bisinisi lalai e sega ni rawata na veivuke vakailavo mai vei ira na baqe kei na so tale na vanua ni vakatubuilavo. E dau dredre talega na rawata na vakatubuilavo ni sa sega ni levu na ivakadei.

2. **Regulatory and Bureaucratic Hurdles (iVakarau ni Lewe ni Matanitu kei na Bureacracy)**: E levu na lawa kei na ivakarau ni matanitu e gadrevi me muri, ka rawa ni vakavuna na vakaloloma ni gauna kei na ilavo. E dau vakavuna talega na dredre ni rawata na laiseni kei na vakatulewa ni bisinisi.

3. **Market Access (Rawati ni Makete)**: E dau dredre me ra rawata na makete levu na bisinisi lalai, vakabibi ena veivanua vakayawa. E dau vakavuna na leqa ni veitosoyaki kei na levu ni ilavo e gadrevi me vakayagataki ena kena vakau na iyaya.

4. **Lack of Business Skills and Knowledge (Dravudravua ni Kila kei na Vuku ni Bisinisi)**: E levu na taukei ni bisinisi lalai e sega ni rawata na ivakatagedegede ni vuli kei na kila me baleta na veiliutaki bisinisi, vakatulewa vakailavo, kei na veika tale eso e gadrevi me cicivaki vinaka kina na bisinisi.

5. **Infrastructure Challenges (Leqa ni iTuvatuva ni Veivakatorocaketaki)**: E levu na vanua e Viti e sega ni vinaka na ituvatuva ni veivakatorocaketaki me vaka na gaunisala, livaliva, wai, kei na internet. E rawa ni vakavuna na vakaloloma ni bisinisi kei na kena sega ni rawarawa na veitosoyaki ni iyaya kei na veiqaravi.

6. **Competition (Veiqati)**: E levu na veiqati mai vei ira na bisinisi lelevu kei na bisinisi mai vanuatani. E dau dredre me ra veiqati kina na bisinisi lalai ena vuku ni levu ni nodra ivakadei kei na levu ni nodra iyau.

7. **Economic Conditions (iTuvaki ni Bula Vakailavo)**: Na draki ni bula vakailavo e Viti e rawa ni vakavuna na dredre ni bisinisi lalai. Na veisau ni isau ni iyaya, levu ni cakacaka, kei na veika tale eso e rawa ni vakavuna na leqa ni bisinisi.

8. **Cultural and Social Factors (iTovo kei na iTuvaki ni Vanua)**: E so na gauna e rawa ni vakavuna na itovo vakavanua kei na ituvaki ni vanua na dredre ni tauyavutaki ni bisinisi. Na veiwekani vakavanua kei na veiqaravi vakavanua e rawa ni vakavuna na leqa ni bisinisi.

E bibi me ra kila na taukei ni bisinisi lalai na veika oqo ka ra vakayagataka na veivuke e rawa ni ra rawata me vukea na nodra bisinisi. Na veivuke mai vei ira na matanitu, veivakatorocaketaki ni bisinisi, kei na veivuke vakavuli e rawa ni vukea na nodra rawata na bisinisi lalai na sasaga ni bula vinaka.

Fijian.text:
E vuqa sara na ka e dau gadrevi me tauyavutaki e dua na bisinisi lailai e Viti. E rawa ni da wasea vakaoqo:

**1. Na iTuvatuva ni Bisinisi:**

* **Na vakasama ni bisinisi:** E dodonu me dua na vakasama vinaka ka rawa ni rawai ira na dauvolivoli.
* **Na ituvatuva ni bisinisi:** E dodonu me dua na ituvatuva vinaka ka vakamatatataki kina na i tuvatuva ni bisinisi, na makete, na veika e gadrevi, kei na veika tale eso.
* **Na veika e gadrevi:** E dodonu me vakarautaki na veika kece e gadrevi me vaka na vale ni bisinisi, iyaya, kei na veika tale eso.

**2. Na Veika Vakailavo:**

* **Na ilavo taumada:** E dodonu me dua na ilavo taumada me tekivu rawa kina na bisinisi.
* **Na ivola ni veidinadinati:** E dodonu me dua na ivola ni veidinadinati me vakaraitaka na i tuvatuva ni bisinisi kei na veika e gadrevi.
* **Na veivuke vakailavo:** E rawa ni kere veivuke vakailavo mai na baqe se na matanitu.

**3. Na Veika Vakalawa:**

* **Na rejisita ni bisinisi:** E dodonu me rejisitataki na bisinisi ena matanitu.
* **Na laiseni ni bisinisi:** E dodonu me dua na laiseni ni bisinisi me rawa ni caka kina na bisinisi.
* **Na veika vakalawa tale eso:** E dodonu me vakamuri na veika vakalawa kece e vauca na bisinisi.

**4. Na Veika Tale Eso:**

* **Na kila-ka kei na maqosa:** E dodonu me dua na kila-ka kei na maqosa ena bisinisi e sa vakarau caka.
* **Na cakacaka vakaukauwa:** E dodonu me dua na cakacaka vakaukauwa me rawa ni toso vinaka kina na bisinisi.
* **Na veitokoni:** E dodonu me dua na veitokoni mai vei ira na wekada, itokani, kei na matavuvale.

E rawa ni da kaya ni sega ni rawarawa na kena tauyavutaki e dua na bisinisi lailai e Viti. Ia, kevaka e dua na vakasama vinaka, na ituvatuva vinaka, kei na cakacaka vakaukauwa, e rawa ni toso vinaka na bisinisi.

Na Legal Aid Commission e Viti e vakarautaka na veiqaravi vakalawa vei ira na lewenivanua era sega ni rawata na veiqaravi vakalawa ena vuku ni nodra ituvaki vakailavo. Na nodra inaki levu e na nodra vakarautaka na veivuke vakalawa vei ira na lewenivanua era gadreva vakalevu, me rawa ni ra vakaitavi ena nodra veika vakalawa ena sala e dodonu, e vakadonui, ka e yaga.

Eso na veiqaravi e vakarautaka na Legal Aid Commission e Viti e okati kina:

1. **Veivuke ena Veika Vakalawa:** E vakarautaka na veivuke vakalawa ena veimataqali kisi, me vakataki ira na kisi ni veiwatini, veika e baleta na gone, veika e baleta na qele, veika e baleta na ilesilesi ni tamata yadua, kei na veika e baleta na lawa ni veicakacaka.

2. **Veivuke ena Veika Vakailavo:** E vukei ira na lewenivanua ena nodra kerekere me baleta na veivuke vakailavo, me vaka na veivuke ena nodra kerekere ni Social Welfare, FNPF (Fiji National Provident Fund), kei na so tale na mataqali veivuke vakailavo.

3. **Veivuke ena Veika Vakadidike:** E vukei ira talega na lewenivanua ena nodra vakadidike ena veika vakalawa, me vaka na kena vakadidiketaki na nodra dodonu vakalawa, na kena vakarautaki na ivakadinadina, kei na kena vakarautaki na ivola ni kerekere kei na so tale na ivakamacala e gadrevi ena veika vakalawa.

4. **Veivakasalataki Vakalawa:** E vakarautaka na veivakasalataki vakalawa vei ira na lewenivanua me baleta na nodra dodonu kei na nodra itavi ena mata ni lawa.

5. **Veivakatawani ena Veilewai:** E rawa talega ni vakarautaka na veivakatawani ena veilewai vei ira na lewenivanua era gadreva na veivuke vakalawa ena nodra kisi.

Na Legal Aid Commission e Viti e sasaga me vakarautaka na veiqaravi vakalawa e veiganiti, e yaga, ka e rawarawa ni raici kina na lewenivanua era gadreva vakalevu na veivuke vakalawa. Na nodra veiqaravi e sega walega ni yaga vei ira na lewenivanua yadudua, ia e tokona talega na vakavakarau dodonu kei na vakatautauvata ena mata ni lawa e Viti.

E vakaraitaka na nodra vakarokoroko na vulagi ki na yalo ni vanua (ka vakabibitaki ena vakabauta vakavanua), ki na turaga ni vanua, kei ira na lewenivanua. In Fijian culture, the concept of "dautama" (or "dautama ni katuba levu ni vale") refers to the traditional Fijian way of building and constructing houses, particularly in rural areas. The "vulagi" you mentioned are the traditional Fijian villagers who are skilled in this art of building.

Now, regarding your question, "Na cava na vuna era dauvakamuria na ivakarau ni dautama o ira na iTaukei vulagi?" which translates to "What is the reason why the iTaukei villagers are skilled in the art of dautama?"

There are several reasons why the iTaukei villagers are skilled in the art of dautama:

1. **Traditional knowledge and skills**: The art of dautama has been passed down from generation to generation through oral tradition and hands-on training. The villagers have learned from their ancestors and have refined their skills over time.
2. **Availability of local materials**: The iTaukei villagers have access to local materials such as wood, bamboo, and thatch, which are readily available in their surroundings. They have developed techniques to harvest, process, and use these materials to build durable and sustainable houses.
3. **Cultural significance**: Building a house is not just about providing shelter; it's also a way to express cultural identity and community values. The iTaukei villagers take pride in their traditional way of building, which is deeply rooted in their cultural heritage.
4. **Practicality and functionality**: The traditional Fijian houses are designed to withstand the tropical climate, with features such as high ceilings, large windows, and thatched roofs that provide natural ventilation and insulation.
5. **Community cooperation**: Building a house is often a communal effort, where villagers come together to help each other. This cooperative approach fosters a sense of community and social bonding.

These factors have contributed to the iTaukei villagers' expertise in the art of dautama, which is an integral part of their cultural identity and traditional way of life.

Na iTaukei vulagi era dauvakamuria na ivakarau ni dautama ena mata ni katuba levu ni vale me vaka na nodra ivakarau vakavanua kei na nodra itovo vakavanua. Na vuna levu era dauvakamuria kina na ivakarau oqo e vu mai na nodra vakabauta kei na nodra maroroya na itovo vakavanua ka ra dau vakayacora ena nodra veimaliwai kei na nodra veidutaitaka na veiwekani.

Ena itovo vakavanua ni iTaukei, na dautama e dua na ivakarau ni vakarokoroko kei na veidokai. Na vulagi e dau vakabibitaki vakalevu ena itovo vakavanua ni iTaukei, ka ra dau vakayacora na itovo ni dautama me vakaraitaka na nodra veikauwaitaki kei na nodra veidokai vua na vulagi. Fijian.text:
Mai na noqu kila me yacova na 2023, na ilavo ni penisioni e Viti e vakarautaki mai na Fiji National Provident Fund (FNPF). Na ilavo ni penisioni e rawa ni duidui me vaka na levu ni ilavo e sa bau vakacurumi (contributions) ki na FNPF, na yabaki ni nona cakacaka na lewenivanua, kei na ivakarau ni penisioni e digitaki.

Na FNPF e solia vei ira na lewenivanua eso na ivakarau ni penisioni me ra digitaka, ka vakatau tiko ena ivakarau ni bula era vinakata ni ra sa vakacegu mai na cakacaka. E rawa ni o digitaka me ra saumi vakamua e dua na iwiliwili ni ilavo (lump sum) ka qai taura na kena vo me vaka na ilavo ni penisioni vakamamaca, se me tauri taucoko me ilavo ni penisioni vakamamaca.

Na kena ivakarau dodonu ni ilavo ni penisioni e rawa ni duidui vakalevu, ka vakatau ena iwiliwili ni ilavo e sa bau vakacurumi ki na nomu akaude ni FNPF, na yabaki o sa bau cakacaka kina, kei na ivakarau ni bula o vinakata ni o sa vakacegu. E tiko talega eso na ituvatuva vou e vakarautaka na FNPF me vukei ira na lewenivanua mera vakarautaka na nodra gauna ni vakacegu, ka vakakina na nodra bula ni mataka.

Me rawa ni o kila vakavinaka na ilavo ni penisioni o na rawata mai na FNPF, e vinaka mo veitaratara sara ga kei na FNPF me baleta na nomu akaude kei na veika e rawa ni o namaka. Era na rawa ni solia vei iko na veika vakailavo e dina ka vakatau ena nomu akaude kei na veika o sa bau vakacuruma yani.

Na ilavo ni peniseni e Viti e dau caka ena veivakatagedegede e vica:

1. Peniseni ni Matua - E dau soli vei ira na lewenivanua era sa yabaki 65 lako cake. 

2. Peniseni ni Malumalumu - E baleti ira na lewenivanua era sa malumalumu tu vakayago se vakayalo ka sega ni rawa ni cakacaka.

3. Peniseni ni Mate ni Cakacaka - E soli vei ira era sa vakaleqai ena gauna ni cakacaka.

4. Peniseni ni Wati/Yada ni sa Mate na Wekana - E soli vua na wati se yada ni tamata cakacaka sa mate.

5. Peniseni ni Gone Luveniyali - E soli vei ira na gone era sa mai luveniyali.

Na ilavo oqo e dau vakadeitaka na Matanitu me vukea na bula ni lewenivanua ena gauna dredre. Ia, e dau vakatau tiko ga na levu ni ilavo e soli ena iyalayala ni bula (poverty threshold) kei na levu ni ilavo e rawata tiko e dua.

1. **Vakarautaka na Qara ni Lovo**: E dodonu me keli e dua na qara ena qele me rauta ni 30cm ki na 60cm na titobu, ka me rauta na kena levu ena ivakarau ni kakana mo vakarautaka.

2. **Vakarautaka na Vatu kei na Bukawaqa**: Digitaka eso na vatu e rawa ni vosota na katakata levu ka kua ni basuka rawa. Vakama e dua na bukawaqa levu ena dela ni qara me vakarautaka na vatu me katakata.

3. **Vakarautaka na Kakana kei na Draunimoli**: Vakarautaka na kakana mo vakasaqa, me vaka na uvi, dalo, ika, se manumanu vuka, ka vakarautaka talega na draunimoli me na tabonaka na kakana.

4. **Vakadavora na Vatu kei na Kakana**: Ni sa katakata vinaka na vatu, tosoya tani eso na qilaiso ka biuta na kakana ena dela ni vatu katakata. E rawa ni o tabaka na kakana ena draunimoli se na iubi ni vudi me taqomaki ka me maroroi kina na kena irairai.

5. **Tabaka na Lovo**: Ni oti na kena biu na kakana, tabaka na lovo ena draunimoli, qele, se na iubi ni vudi me kua ni curu na ea se me drodro na wai. Na kena tabonaki vinaka e vukea me maroroi na katakata ka vakavuna na kakana me saqa vakamalua.

6. **Vakawaqa na Lovo**: Me saqa tiko na kakana ena vica na aua, me vaka na levu kei na mataqali kakana. E rawa ni yacova mai na 2 ki na 8 na aua se sivia, me vaka na levu ni lovo.

7. **Vakasuka na Lovo**: Ni sa nanamaki ni sa vakarau na kakana, dolava vakamalua na lovo ka vakasuka na draunimoli kei na qele. Vakarautaka me kua ni vakacacani na kakana ena kena vakasukai.

8. **Vakarautaka na Kakana**: Ni sa vakasukai oti na kakana, e rawa ni vakarautaki me ra kania.

3. **Gasau**: E gadrevi na gasau me vakaduria kina na kakana.
4. **Drauni niu**: E gadrevi na drauni niu me ubia kina na kakana.

4. **Kubou**:

2. Gather information: Collect any relevant documents or evidence related to the issue. This could include photos, receipts, or any other supporting materials.

3. Find the right department: Different issues are handled by different government departments. For example, issues related to taxes would be handled by the Fiji Revenue and Customs Service, while issues related to the environment would be handled by the Ministry of Waterways and Environment.

Ni o via taura na veivuke vaka ilavo mai vua na matanitu me baleta na tiko vakalolovira, e bibi mo vakarautaka eso na itukutuku kei na ivola me vakadeitaka na nomu kerekere. Na ivakarau ni veika e gadrevi e rawa ni duidui mai na dua na vanua ki na dua tale, ia e so na ivakarau raraba e rawa ni o vakarautaka:

2. **Ivakadinadina ni Yalomatua**: Oqo e rawa ni oka kina na nomu pasipote, laiseni ni draiva, se dua tale na ivola ni vakadinadina ni yalomatua e vakadeitaka na nomu ituvaki vakaloloma.

3. **Ivakadinadina ni Tiko Vakaloloma**: E rawa ni oka kina na ivola mai na tabana ni matanitu, na veika e volai ena niusiveva, se na ivakadinadina ni veivakacacani, veivakasaurarataki, se veivakalolomataki o sotava.

4. **Ivakadinadina ni Tiko Vakailavo**: Oqo e rawa ni oka kina na nomu ivakadinadina ni tiko vakailavo, me vaka na nomu ivola ni baqe, ivakadinadina ni cakacaka, se ivakadinadina ni sega ni rawa ni o cakacaka ena vuku ni nomu ituvaki vakaloloma.

5. **Ivakamacala ni Vuni Kerekere**: E bibi mo vola e dua na ivola se dua na ivakamacala ni vuni o gadreva kina na veivuke vaka ilavo, ka vakamacalataka vakamatata na nomu ituvaki kei na vuna o gadreva kina na veivuke.

6. **Ivakadinadina ni Vakawati kei na Vuvale**: Kevaka e yaga, vakarautaka na ivakadinadina ni vakawati, na ivola ni sucu ni luvemu, se dua tale na ivakadinadina ni veiwekani.

7. **Ivakadinadina ni Vakadidike ni Yavu ni Lawa**: Kevaka o sa vakayacora e dua na kerekere me baleta na tiko vakaloloma se dua tale na ituvaki vakalawa, vakarautaka na ivakadinadina ni nomu kerekere kei na kena ituvaki ena gauna oqo.

8. **Ivakadinadina ni Bula Vinaka kei na Vakasama**: Kevaka e gadrevi, vakarautaka na ivakadinadina ni nomu bula vinaka kei na vakasama, me vaka na ivola mai na vuniwai se na dauvakasama.

Ni o sa vakarautaka oti na veika e gadrevi, vakarautaki iko talega me vakayacora e dua na veitalanoa se dua na veivosaki kei na tabana ni matanitu e dau vakarautaka na veivuke vaka ilavo, me rawa ni o vakamacalataka vakavinaka na nomu ituvaki kei na vuna o gadreva kina na veivuke. Nanuma ni na vinakati mo muria na ivakarau ni kerekere ka vakarautaka na veika e gadrevi ena gauna kei na sala e gadrevi.

To separate the stories of the people of Fiji from the iTaukei would be like trying to separate the threads of a traditional Fijian masi (tapa cloth) - it would be impossible to untangle the intricate patterns and designs that make up the fabric of Fijian culture.

In short, the stories of the people of Fiji and the iTaukei are inextricably linked, and they continue to play a vital role in shaping the identity, culture, and traditions of Fiji as a nation.

Fijian.text: O cei ko Ratu Sukuna?

Fijian.text: O cei ko Ratu Sir Lala Sukuna? Ratu Sir Lala Sukuna is a highly respected figure in Fijian history. He was a statesman, soldier, and chief who played a significant role in shaping modern Fiji. Born in 1888, Sukuna was the first Fijian to receive a university education, studying at Oxford University in the United Kingdom. He served in both World War I and World War II, and was knighted by King George VI in 1946. After the war, Sukuna became a key figure in Fijian politics, serving as a member of the Legislative Council and later as the first Fijian to be appointed to the Executive Council. Hot stone massage is a type of massage therapy that involves the use of smooth, heated stones. The stones are usually made of basalt, a type of volcanic rock that retains heat well.

**How hot stone massage is performed:**

1. **Preparation:** The massage therapist will heat the stones in a professional stone heater to a temperature between 120-150 degrees Fahrenheit (49-66 degrees Celsius). They will also prepare the massage area with a comfortable table and soothing music.
2. **Application of oil:** The therapist will apply massage oil to your skin to reduce friction and allow the stones to glide smoothly.
3. **Placement of stones:** The therapist will place the heated stones on specific points of your body, such as your back, legs, arms, and hands. They may also hold stones in their hands to massage your muscles.
4. **Massage techniques:** The therapist will use a variety of massage techniques, such as long strokes, circular movements, and kneading, to work the muscles and promote relaxation.
5. **Removal of stones:** Once the massage is complete, the therapist will carefully remove the stones from your body.

**Benefits of hot stone massage:**

* **Relieves muscle tension and pain:** The heat from the stones helps to relax muscles and increase blood flow, which can reduce pain and stiffness.
* **Promotes relaxation and stress relief:** The warmth and pressure of the stones can help to calm the nervous system and promote a sense of well-being.
* **Improves circulation:** The heat from the stones can dilate blood vessels, which improves circulation and oxygen delivery to the muscles.
* **Reduces stress and anxiety:** The relaxing effects of hot stone massage can help to reduce stress and anxiety levels.

**Precautions:**

* Hot stone massage is not suitable for everyone, including pregnant women, people with certain medical conditions, and those with sensitive skin.
* It's important to choose a qualified and experienced massage therapist who is trained in hot stone massage techniques.
* If you experience any discomfort or pain during the massage, let the therapist know immediately.

Eso na vuna bibi e dau vakayacori kina na ivakarau oqo era sa vakamacalataki e ra:

1. **Veivakarokorokotaki kei na Veidokai:** Na nodra vakayacani na gone vei ira na wekana na tama e dua na sala ni veivakarokorokotaki kei na veidokai vei ira na lewe ni vuvale. Oqo e vakaraitaka na nodra bibi na veiwekani kei na nodra itavi ena bula ni gone.

2. **Veivakabauti kei na Veitokoni:** Na vakayacani e vakaraitaka na veivakabauti ni na tokoni na gone ena nona bula mai vei ira na wekana. E vakaraitaka na nodra vakarau na wekana me ra tokoni koya ena veika vakayalo, vakailavo, kei na vakasama.

3. **Veivakamareqeti kei na Veivakamemori:** Eso na gauna, na vakayacani e vakayacori me vakananumi se vakamareqeti e dua na wekana sa yali. Oqo e dua na sala ni nodra vakabulabulataki tiko ga na nodra irogorogo kei na nodra itavi ena vuvale.

4. **Veivakavulici kei na Veivakauqeti:** Na vakayacani e rawa ni vakavulici koya na gone ena nona itavi kei na nona vanua ena vuvale kei na vanua vakavanua. E vakaraitaka na nodra nuitaki na gone me ra muria na yavu ni nodra qase kei na nodra itovo vinaka.

5. **Veivakabulabulataki ni Veitikina Vakavanua kei na Vosa:** Na vakayacani e vakabulabulataka na vosa kei na itukutuku vakavanua, ni o ira na gone era na vulica na kena ibalebale kei na kena italanoa ena nodra vakayacani.

6. **Veivakaduiduitaki kei na Veiyalayalati:** E vakaraitaka na nodra veiyalayalati na gone kei na nodra mataqali, ka vakaduiduitaka na nodra itutu vakavanua kei na nodra veiwekani.

In Fijian culture, the concept of "sucu" or "tabu" is deeply rooted in the traditional way of life. It is a complex system of respect, authority, and social hierarchy that governs the behavior and interactions among individuals, particularly within the family and community.

In the context of your question, "Ni sucu na gone ulumatua iTaukei" refers to the respect and reverence accorded to the elderly, particularly the grandparents, in iTaukei (indigenous Fijian) society. The elderly are considered the custodians of traditional knowledge, culture, and values, and are therefore held in high esteem.

The question "na cava na vuna dauvakayacani kina na gone vei ira na wekana na tama ni gone" can be translated to "What is the reason for the lack of respect shown by some children towards their grandparents?"

There are several possible reasons for this phenomenon:

1. **Cultural erosion**: The influence of modernization, urbanization, and globalization has led to a decline in traditional values and cultural practices. As a result, some young people may not fully understand or appreciate the importance of respecting their elders.
2. **Generational gap**: The differences in values, beliefs, and lifestyles between older and younger generations can lead to a disconnect, making it challenging for some children to relate to their grandparents.
3. **Lack of communication**: In some cases, there may be a lack of effective communication between grandparents and grandchildren, leading to misunderstandings and a breakdown in relationships.
4. **Changing family dynamics**: The structure of Fijian families has undergone significant changes in recent years, with many children growing up in nuclear families or single-parent households. This shift can lead to a decline in the traditional extended family system, where grandparents played a more prominent role.
5. **Influence of technology**: The widespread use of technology, such as social media and video games, can distract children from interacting with their grandparents and learning about their cultural heritage.

It is essential to address these issues and promote intergenerational understanding and respect within Fijian families. By doing so, we can help preserve the rich cultural heritage of the iTaukei people and ensure that the values of respect, tradition, and community are passed down to future generations.

prompting_state.prompt: O cei ko Ratu 'Sir' Kamisese Mara?

Fijian.text:
Ratu Sir Kamisese Mara (6 Mei 1920 – 18 April 2004) o se tasi o taitai sili ona lauiloa ma fa'aaloalogia i le talafa'asolopito o Fiji ma le Pasefika. O ia o se tasi o tama o le malo tuto'atasi o Fiji, ma sa avea ma ulua'i Palemia o Fiji mai le 1970, ina ua maua e Fiji lona tuto'atasi mai Peretania, se'ia oo i le 1992, ma toe avea ma Palemia mai le 1992 se'ia oo i le 1997. Sa ia tautua foi o le Peresetene o Fiji mai le 1993 se'ia oo i le 2000.

O Mara sa lauiloa mo lona atamai i mataupu fa'apolokiki, ma sa ia taumafai e fa'aleleia ma fa'atumauina le filemu ma le mautu i totonu o Fiji, aemaise lava i le va o tagata Fijian ma Indo-Fijians, o ni vaega etniko e lua e tele i le atunu'u. E ui i lona taumafai e fa'atino le fa'aleleia ma le fa'atonutonu, ae na feagai ma lu'itau tetele, e aofia ai ma fa'alavelave fa'apolokiki ma le tamaoaiga, fa'apea ma vevesi fa'atupu fa'alavelave i le va o vaega etniko eseese.

O lona tautua i le atunu'u ma le itulagi o le Pasefika sa lautele ma loloto, ma sa ia maua ai le fa'aaloalo tele mai le lalolagi atoa. O Mara sa fa'aigoaina i le suafa "Ratu" lea e fa'ailoa ai lona tulaga maualuga i le aganu'u vaka-Viti, ma sa fa'aigoa foi o ia i le suafa "Sir" ina ua fa'aigoaina o ia i le Aiga o le Malo o Peretania mo ana tautua.

E ui ina ua mavae lona taimi i le paoa, ae o lo'o tumau pea le fa'aaloalo ma le manatua o Ratu Sir Kamisese Mara e le gata i le atunu'u o Fiji ae fa'apea foi i le itulagi lautele o le Pasefika, ona o lona sao taua i le fa'aleleia o le soifua lautele, fa'apolokiki, ma le tamaoaiga i le itulagi.

prompting_state.prompt: O cei ko Ratu 'Sir' Kamisese Mara?

Fijian.text:
O Ratu Sir Kamisese Mara e dua na turaga ni vanua ka liuliu ni matanitu mai Viti. E sucu ena yabaki 1920 ka mate ena 2004. Eso na ka bibi me baleti koya:

- E imatai ni Paraiminisita ni Viti ni sa rawata na tu vakataki koya ena 1970. E veiliutaki me yacova na 1992.
- E a vukea vakalevu na kena rawati na tu galala vakapolitiki kei na bula sautu ni Viti.
- E a vunivola tudei ni Matabose Cokovata ni Pasifika (South Pacific Forum) mai na 1973 ki na 1990s.
- E a Peresitedi talega ni Viti mai 1993 ki 2000.
- E kilai levu me vaka e dua na dauniveivakasalataki vuku ka dau cakacaka vakaukauwa me baleta na toso ni nona vanua.
- E a soli vua na itutu vakaturaga na "Ratu" kei na itutu vakaPeritania na "Sir" baleta na nona veiqaravi uasivi.

O Ratu Mara e dua na iliuliu dokai sara ka bibi ena istoriya ni Viti, ka vakauqeti ira vakalevu na nona tamata me ra toso ki liu.

Ratu Mara was a member of the Tui Nayau, the traditional ruling family of the Lau Islands in eastern Fiji. He was educated at the University of Otago in New Zealand and later at Oxford University in the United Kingdom.

During his political career, Ratu Mara played a key role in Fiji's transition from a British colony to an independent nation. He was a strong advocate for Fijian nationalism and worked to promote the interests of indigenous Fijians.

Ratu Mara was also a respected figure in the Pacific region and played a leading role in regional organizations such as the Pacific Islands Forum.

He was knighted by Queen Elizabeth II in 1969 and was awarded several honorary degrees from universities around the world.

Ratu Sir Kamisese Mara is still remembered and respected in Fiji and the Pacific region for his leadership and contributions to the development of his country and the region.

A question about Fijian politics!

Na cava na vuna era tauyavutaka na PAP (People Alliance Party) refers to the reasons why the People's Alliance Party (PAP) was formed.

Ko ira na lewe taumada ni SDLP (Soqosoqo Duavata Ni Lewe Ni Vanua Party) means "What are the main principles of the SDL Party?"

Here are the answers:

**People's Alliance Party (PAP)**

The People's Alliance Party was formed in 2020 by Sitiveni Rabuka, a former Prime Minister of Fiji, and other like-minded individuals. The main reasons for its formation were:

1. To provide an alternative to the ruling FijiFirst party, which had been in power since 2014.
2. To promote democratic values, good governance, and transparency in government.
3. To address the concerns of indigenous Fijians, who felt their rights and interests were being neglected.
4. To promote national unity and reconciliation among Fiji's diverse ethnic groups.

**Soqosoqo Duavata Ni Lewe Ni Vanua Party (SDL)**

The SDL Party, also known as the United Fiji Party, was formed in 2001 by Laisenia Qarase, a former Prime Minister of Fiji. The main principles of the SDL Party are:

1. To promote the interests and rights of indigenous Fijians, who make up about 57% of Fiji's population.
2. To protect and preserve Fiji's traditional culture, customs, and way of life.
3. To promote economic development and self-reliance for indigenous Fijians.
4. To foster national unity and cooperation among all ethnic groups in Fiji.

It's worth noting that the SDL Party was dissolved in 2009 after the military coup led by Frank Bainimarama, and many of its members went on to form the Social Democratic Liberal Party (SODELPA), which is currently one of the main opposition parties in Fiji.

prompting_state.prompt: Iko cakava vakacava na kai vakasoso?

Fijian.text:
Na kai vakasoso e dua na ivakarau ni vakasaqaqa se vakarautaki ni kakana e kilai levu ena Pasifika, vakabibi ena veiyanuyanu e Viti. E vakayagataki kina na kena vakasosoi se vakasaqari na kakana ena dua na lovo se qeleqele ni buka waqa sa vakarautaki tu. Na kena vakarautaki e rawa ni duidui me vaka na vanua kei na ivakarau ni bula, ia e tiko eso na ivakavuvuli vovou e dau muria na lewenivanua ena kena vakarautaki. Oqo e so na ivakavuvuli ena kena vakarautaki na kai vakasoso:

1. **Vakarautaki ni Lovo**: Na lovo e dua na qara ni buka waqa e keli ena qele, ka vakarautaki kina na vatu me ra katakata vinaka. Na vatu e taura na katakata ka solia tiko na veikatakata ena gauna e sa vakasosoi kina na kakana.

2. **Vakarautaki ni Kakana**: Na kakana e rawa ni wili kina na ika, lewe ni manumanu (me vakataki na vuaka, me, se moa), vutu, dalo, yabia, kei na so tale na kakana dina ni vanua. E dau vakarautaki na kakana me vakasosoi ena nona vakamamacataki vinaka ka vakarautaki me vaka na kena gadrevi.

3. **Vakayagataki ni Draunimoli**: E dau vakayagataki na draunimoli (lau ni niu) se draunivonovono me ibulibuli se me ibinibini ena kakana, me maroroi kina na kena irairai kei na kena tatadra ena gauna e sa vakasosoi oti.

4. **Vakasoso ena Lovo**: Ni sa katakata vinaka na vatu ena lovo, sa qai biu kina na kakana e sa vakarautaki oti, ka ubi vinaka ena draunimoli se draunivonovono. E rawa ni vakayagataki talega na qele se iubi ni lovo me maroroi kina na kena katakata. Na kakana e dau tiko ena lovo me vica na aua me yacova ni sa vakarau me kani.

5. **Vakayagataki ni Masima kei na Vakasaqaqa Vakavanua**: E rawa ni vakayagataki na masima kei na so na vakasaqaqa vakavanua me vakavinakataka na tovo ni kakana, ia e duidui na kena vakayagataki me vaka na vanua kei na ivakarau ni bula.

Na kai vakasoso e kilai ena nona tatadra kei na nona irairai vinaka, ka vakaraitaka na veivakabauti kei na ivakarau ni bula ni Pasifika. E dua na iwase levu ni soqo kei na magiti vakavanua, ka vakaraitaka na nodra veiwekani kei na nodra veikilai na lewenivanua.

prompting_state.prompt: Iko cakava vakacava na kai vakasoso?

Fijian.text:
Oqo e dua na ivakamacala lekaleka ni kai vakasoso:

1. Vakarautaka na soso (lolo ni niu, suka, masima kei na wai)
2. Tavia na soso me katakata vinaka
3. Cereka na kai ki na veiiwasewase lalai
4. Biuta na kai ki na soso katakata ka vakawaicalataka me rauta ni 30 na miniti
5. Cereka na vuanikau (vudi, cassava se dalo) ka qai biuta ki na soso
6. Vakawaicalataka tale me vica na miniti me drodro kina na soso
7. Kania ni sa buta vinaka na kai kei na vuanikau

Oqori ga e dua na ivakaraitaki ni sala ni cakacakataki ni kai vakasoso. E rawa ni duidui na kena caka vei ira eso tale na veimatavuvale se vanua e Viti.

* "Iko" means "what" or "which"
* "cakava" means "news" or "information"
* "vakacava" is a question marker, similar to "ka" in Hindi or "ne" in Japanese
* "na" is a possessive marker, indicating "of" or "about"
* "kai" means "village"
* "vakasoso" is a noun phrase meaning "the village" or "our village"

So, if someone asks you "Iko cakava vakacava na kai vakasoso?", they're inquiring about the latest news or gossip from the village!

prompting_state.prompt: Iko cakava vakacava na kai vakasoso?

Fijian.text:
Na cakacaka ni kai vakasoso e dau vakatau ena itovo, ivakarau, kei na ituvatuva ni nodra bula. E so na ka era dau cakava na kai vakasoso e rawa ni okati kina na:

1. **Veivukei kei na Veikauwaitaki**: Era dau veivukei vakalevu ena nodra itikotiko, veivukei ena gauna ni leqa, kei na veivakabulai.

2. **Veivakatorocaketaki ni Bula**: Era dau vakayagataka na nodra kila-ka kei na nodra taledi me ra vukea kina na nodra itikotiko me vakatorocaketaki na bula vakayago kei na bula vakayalo.

3. **Veivakatorocaketaki ni Vanua**: Era dau vakaitavi ena cakacaka ni veivakatorocaketaki ni vanua, me vaka na tara vale, vakavinakataki ni gaunisala, kei na so tale na cakacaka ni veivakatorocaketaki.

4. **Veivakatorocaketaki ni Vuli**: Era dau vakaitavi ena veivakatorocaketaki ni vuli, me vaka na veivuke ena vuli ni gone, veivakavulici ena veika e baleta na bula vakayago kei na bula vakayalo.

5. **Veivakatorocaketaki ni Bula Vakayalo**: Era dau vakaitavi ena veika vakayalo, me vaka na veivakavulici ena lotu, veivuke ena veika vakalotu, kei na veivakabulai vakayalo.

6. **Veivakatorocaketaki ni Bula Vakailavo**: Era dau vakaitavi ena veivakatorocaketaki ni bula vakailavo, me vaka na veivuke ena kena vakatorocaketaki na bisinisi lalai, veivuke ena kena vakatorocaketaki na cakacaka, kei na veivakatorocaketaki ni ituvatuva ni bula vakailavo.

Na cakacaka ni kai vakasoso e dau vakatau talega ena nodra ituvatuva ni bula kei na nodra gagadre me ra vukea na nodra itikotiko kei na nodra vanua.

prompting_state.prompt: Na cava beka meu cakava mena rawa kina na card ni basi ni nodra na malumalumu?

Fijian.text:
Kevaka o vinakata me rawa na card ni basi me baleta na nodra na malumalumu (ena so na vanua e kilai tani ga oqo me disability bus pass se concessionary travel card), e dodonu mo muria na veika e ra:

1. **Vakadidike ena Veika e Gadrevi:** Vakadikeva na veika e gadrevi me rawa na card ni basi ni nodra na malumalumu ena nomu vanua se tauni. Na veika e gadrevi e rawa ni duidui mai na dua na vanua ki na dua tale, ia e vakabauta ni oka kina na ivakadinadina ni malumalumu, na ivola ni vuniwai, se na ivakadinadina ni nomu tiko ena dua na porokaramu ni veivuke vakailavo.

2. **Taura na Fomu ni Kerekere:** Taura na fomu ni kerekere mai na tabana ni veivuke vakailavo, tabana ni veitosoyaki ni lewenivanua, se mai na website ni koroturaga ni nomu vanua. E so na vanua e rawa ni o vakacuruma na nomu kerekere ena initaneti.

3. **Vakarautaka na Veika e Gadrevi:** Vakarautaka na veika e gadrevi me vaka na ivakadinadina ni nomu malumalumu, itukutuku vakavuniwai, kei na veika tale eso e gadrevi ena fomu ni kerekere. E rawa talega ni gadrevi mo vakarautaka na itukutuku vakailavo se na ivakadinadina ni nomu tiko ena dua na porokaramu ni veivuke vakailavo.

1. **Vakadidike Vakavinaka:** Ni bera ni o volia na qele, vakarautaka e dua na vakadidike lolovira me baleta na qele oya. Oqo e okati kina na kena vakadidiketaki na ituvaki ni qele, na kena itikotiko, na kena vakayagataki tiko ena gauna oqo kei na veika e rawa ni vakayagataki kina ena gauna mai muri, kei na kena ivakatagedegede ni veivoli.

6. **Vakadeitaka na Veika Vakailavo:** Vakadeitaka ni sa tu vakarau na nomu ituvatuva vakailavo me baleta na volivoli, oka kina na kena saumi na ilavo ni volivoli, na vakacavacava, kei na so tale na isau e rawa ni basika.

It seems like you're asking about how to learn the Fijian language, specifically the iTaukei dialect. Here are some steps to help you get started:

1. Find resources: Look for Fijian language learning books, online courses, or mobile apps. Some popular resources include "Fijian Dictionary" by Rusiate T. Nayacakalou and "Fijian Language Course" by the Fiji Museum.

2. Learn the basics: Start with the Fijian alphabet, pronunciation, and basic grammar rules. Familiarize yourself with common phrases and vocabulary.

3. Practice speaking: Try to find a language exchange partner or a tutor who is a native speaker of the iTaukei dialect. This will help you improve your pronunciation and conversational skills.

4. Immerse yourself: Listen to Fijian music, watch Fijian movies or TV shows, and read Fijian literature. This will help you get used to the sounds and rhythms of the language.

5. Be patient and consistent: Learning a new language takes time and effort. Make sure to practice regularly and don't get discouraged if you make mistakes.

prompting_state.prompt: Daucaka vakacava na veiduguci ena bula vaka itaukei?

Fijian.text:
Na veiduguci ena bula vaka iTaukei e dua na ka bibi ka vakayagataki vakalevu ena nodra bula na iTaukei mai Viti. E vakaraitaka na veivakarokorokotaki, veivakamalumalumutaki, kei na veivakavinavinakataki ena veika duidui e yaco ena bula ni vanua. Eso na kena ivakaraitaki e okati kina na veiqaravi ena gauna ni vakamau, veibulu, solevu, kei na so tale na soqo vakavanua.

1. **Veivakamalumalumutaki (Sevusevu):** E dua na ivakarau bibi ni veiduguci na sevusevu, ka vakayacori ena gauna ni curu ki na dua na koro se vanua me vakaraitaki kina na veidokai kei na kerekere me vakadonui na nodra tiko ena vanua oya. E vakayagataki kina na yaqona (kava) me isevu, ka soli vei ira na turaga ni vanua se vei ira na liuliu ni koro.

2. **Vakamau:** Ena gauna ni vakamau, e dau vakayacori na veiduguci ena kena soli na iyau vakavanua, ka vakatokai me "sokalou" se "vakasobu," ki na vuvale ni yalewa. Oqo e ivakaraitaki ni veivakarokorokotaki kei na veivakavinavinakataki vei ira na vuvale ni yalewa ena nodra solia na luvedra yalewa me watidra na tagane.

3. **Veibulu:** Ena gauna ni veibulu, e dau vakayacori talega na veiduguci ena kena soli na iyau vakavanua kei na kakana vei ira na vuvale e yaco tiko vei ira na mate. Oqo e ivakaraitaki ni veivakacegui kei na veivakadonui ena gauna dredre.

4. **Solevu kei na Soqo Vakavanua:** Ena solevu kei na soqo vakavanua, e dau vakayacori na veiduguci ena kena soli na iyau vakavanua, kakana, kei na yaqona me ivakaraitaki ni veivakavinavinakataki, veivakarokorokotaki, kei na veitokoni ena veika e yaco.

Na veiduguci e sega walega ni vakaraitaka na veivakarokorokotaki kei na veivakavinavinakataki, ia e tara talega na bula vakavanua kei na veiwekani ena kedra maliwa na iTaukei. E vakarabailevutaka na veidokai, veivakararamataki, kei na veivakabauti ena kedra maliwa na lewenivanua, ka vakadeitaka na bula vakacegu kei na veitokani ena loma ni vanua.

prompting_state.prompt: Daucaka vakacava na veiduguci ena bula vaka itaukei?

Fijian.text:
Ena bula vakavanua vakaViti, e dau vakayagataki vakalevu na veiduguci me vakaraitaki kina na veivakarokorokotaki, na loloma kei na veiwekani. 

Eso na kena ivakaraitaki na veiduguci e Viti:

1. Veiduguci ni veikidavaki - ni sota e rua na tamata, rau dau veiduguci me rau kidavaki kina. 

2. Veiduguci ni vakavinavinaka - ni caka e dua na ka vinaka vei iko, e dodonu mo veiduguci mo vakavinavinakataka kina.

3. Veiduguci ni veivosoti - kevaka e caka e dua na cala, rau qai veiduguci na tamata me rau veivosoti kina.

4. Veiduguci ni veitalatala - ni dua e via vosa vei iko, drau veiduguci taumada ni bera ni vosa.

5. Veiduguci ni veivakamoceri - ni tiko e dua na soqo ni mate, era dau veiduguci na lewe ni vanua me vakaraitaki kina na veivakamoceri.

E vakaraitaka na veiduguci na veimaliwai vinaka kei na veivakarokorokotaki ena bula vakavanua vakaViti. E umani vata kina na yalo ni veilomani, veiciqomi kei na veikauwaitaki.

The TLTB is responsible for leasing iTaukei land to tenants for various purposes, including agriculture, residential, commercial, and industrial use.

The TLTB is governed by the iTaukei Land Trust Act, which sets out the powers and functions of the Board. The Board is made up of members appointed by the Minister responsible for iTaukei affairs, who are representatives of various iTaukei organizations and stakeholders.

* Issuing leases for iTaukei land to tenants
* Collecting rent and other payments from tenants
* Ensuring that tenants comply with the terms and conditions of their leases
* Resolving disputes between tenants and customary owners
* Providing advice and assistance to customary owners on land management and development issues

The TLTB also has a role in promoting the sustainable use and development of iTaukei land, and in ensuring that the benefits of land use are shared equitably among the customary owners.

Na cakacaka levu ni TLTB e vakarautaka ka maroroya na qele ni iTaukei (qele vakavanua) ena yasana ni veika vakailavo, vakalawalawa, kei na veika vakavanua, ka vakaraitaka na nodra bula vinaka na iTaukei (lewenivanua dina ni Fiji) kei na nodra kawa ena veigauna mai muri.

Eso na cakacaka bibi ni TLTB e okati kina:

1. **Maroroi kei na Veivakatorocaketaki ni Qele ni iTaukei:** Na TLTB e maroroya na qele ni iTaukei ka vakarautaka na kena vakayagataki vakavuku me baleta na veivakatorocaketaki vakailavo, ni qele oqo e sega ni rawa ni volitaki se vakacavacavataki vakadua.

2. **Veivakadonui ena Vakayagataki ni Qele:** E vakarautaka na veivakadonui kei na veidinadinati me baleta na vakayagataki ni qele, me vaka na lease (tuvatuva ni qele) ki na nona iTaukei se vei ira na sega ni iTaukei, ena inaki ni veivoli, veivakatorocaketaki, se vakayagataki vakailavo.

3. **Veivakaduiduitaki ni Qele kei na Veivakatorocaketaki:** E vakaitavi ena veivakaduiduitaki ni qele me rawa ni vakayagataki vakavinaka ka vakatorocaketaki, ka vakarautaka na veivuke vakailavo kei na veiqaravi vakatekinikau vei ira na iTaukei ena nodra vakayagataka na nodra qele.

4. **Veivakabulabulataki kei na Veivakasama Vakailavo:** E vakarautaka na veivakasama vakailavo kei na veivuke vei ira na iTaukei ena nodra vakayagataka na nodra qele me rawa ni ra rawata kina na yaga vakailavo, ka vakarautaka na veivakabulabulataki ena nodra bula.

5. **Veitaqomaki kei na Veisaututaki ni Yaga ni Qele:** E taqomaka na yaga ni qele ni iTaukei ka vakarautaka na veisaututaki ni yaga ni qele ena sala e taqomaka kina na nodra dodonu na iTaukei ka vakarautaka na yaga vakailavo vei ira.

Na iTaukei Land Trust Board e tiko kina na itavi bibi ena veimaroroi kei na veivakatorocaketaki ni qele ni iTaukei, ka vakarautaka na sala me ra rawata kina na iTaukei na yaga vakailavo mai na nodra qele ka taqomaka tiko ga na nodra dodonu kei na nodra itavi vakavanua.

1. **Maroroi ni Qele ni Taukei**: TLTB e qarava na maroroi ni qele ni taukei me vaka na lawa kei na veika e gadrevi ena nodra yaga na taukei ni qele.

5. **Veivuke ena Veika Vakailavo**: TLTB e vukea na taukei ni qele ena kena rawati na i lavo mai na lisi kei na laiseni, ka vakadeitaka ni sauma vakavinaka na lisi o ira na vakayagataka na qele.

6. **Veivakatorocaketaki kei na Vuli**: TLTB e dau vakayacora na veivakatorocaketaki kei na vuli me baleta na taukei ni qele me rawa ni ra kila vinaka na veika e baleta na nodra qele kei na kena vakayagataki.
